Description:
Annotation on the envelope: "Missale"

- First subfolder (addressed to "Herrn Prof. Dr. Hans Gerhard Evers Deutsche Akademie Kazernestraat" from the Stadsbibliotheek of Antwerp):
    - Photos of Rubens engravings in the Breviarium (1614)
- Second subfolder (Annotation: "III [illegible] in Grasse"):
    - Envelope from E. Plietzsch (Berlin) dated 12.04.1943 with photos of engravings
    - Envelope from Plitt (Nuremberg) with photos of engravings
    - Envelope from Hannover dated 04.01.1943 with photos of engravings 
    - Envelope from J. Evers (LÃ¼beck) with photos of engravings from Missali (1614-1618), Oktavmissale (1614) and Michel Lasne Missale (1619)
    - Envelope from Munich dated 15.01.1943 with photos of engravings from Missale (1613) and other Missali
    - Envelope from Stuttgart dated 11.11.1942 with photos of engravings from Missale (1627), Missale (1629) and undated Missale
    - List of the chapters in "Rubens" by Evers
- Photos of engravings from different Missali glued on cardboards
